quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to declare variable a of type int and then assign 7 as its value:
[!raw!]
{0} a;
a {1} 7;

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Declaring Variables[/h1]

You have the option to assign a value to the variable at the time you declare the variable or to declare it and assign a value later.
You can also change the value of a variable.
[b]Some examples:[/b] [code format="cpp"]int a; 
int b = 42;

a = 10;
b = 3;[/code]

[h1]Accepting User Input [/h1]

The following program prompts the user to input a number and stores it in the variable [b]a[/b]: [code format="cpp" codeId="936"]#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
   int a;
   cout << "Please enter a number \n";
   [b]cin >> a;[/b]

   return 0;
}[/code]
When the program runs, it displays the message "Please enter a number", and then waits for the user to enter a number and press Enter, or Return. 
The entered number is stored in the variable [b]a[/b].
[note]The program will wait for as long as the user needs to type in a number.[/note]

